
Movie Theater Ticket Booking System

This is a command-line interface (CLI) program for a movie theater ticket booking system. The program allows users to view the available movies, select a movie, select a showtime, and choose their seats.

The program is written in Python and uses object-oriented programming (OOP) concepts to implement the ticket booking system.

Getting Started

Clone or download the repository to your local machine.
Open the terminal/command prompt and navigate to the directory where the code is located.
Run the command python ticket_booking_system.py to start the program.

Usage

When the program starts, the user is presented with a list of available movies to choose from.
The user selects a movie by entering the movie ID.
The program displays the showtimes for the selected movie and prompts the user to choose a showtime by entering the showtime ID.
The program displays the seating arrangement for the selected showtime and prompts the user to select their seats by entering the row and column numbers of the seats.
The program confirms the booking and displays the ticket information.

Features

View available movies
Select a movie
View showtimes for the selected movie
Select a showtime
View seating arrangement for the selected showtime
Select seats
Book tickets
View ticket information
Exit the program
